<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">Well... I think nowadays we&apos;re supposed to apply situational ethics here, aren&apos;t we? To wit... :<br/><br/> If Steinbeck was a Liberal, we&apos;re supposed to excuse <a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">Well... I think nowadays we're supposed to apply situational ethics here, aren't we? To wit... :<br /><br /> If Steinbeck was a Liberal, we're supposed to excuse him by saying that"he was a man of his time", (like Woodrow Wilson belonging to the KKK, etc.).<br /><br />But if he was a Conservative, then we're supposed to immediately write him off completely as being a racist sexist bigoted homophobe, etc.<br /><br />Did I get that right? My PC-Ometer hasn't been calibrated recently so it may be a little rusty...<br /><a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
</span>
